import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    airports_by_country = data.groupby('country').size().reset_index(name='counts')
    airports_by_country = airports_by_country.sort_values(by='counts', ascending=False)
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.bar(airports_by_country['country'], airports_by_country['counts'], color='blue')
    ax.set_xlabel('Country')
    ax.set_ylabel('Number of Airports')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of airports by country?')
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.show()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    state_counts = data.groupby('state').size().reset_index(name='counts')
    state_counts = state_counts.sort_values(by='counts', ascending=False)
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 6))
    ax.bar(state_counts['state'], state_counts['counts'], color='blue')
    ax.set_xlabel('State/Province')
    ax.set_ylabel('Number of Airports')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of airports by state/province?')
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.tight_layout()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.scatter(data['longitude'], data['latitude'], s=5, alpha=0.5)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of airports by latitude and longitude?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Longitude')
    plt.ylabel('Latitude')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
from wordcloud import WordCloud

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    wc = WordCloud(width=800, height=400, max_words=200, background_color='white').generate(' '.join(data['name']))
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    plt.imshow(wc, interpolation='bilinear')
    plt.axis('off')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of airport names?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['iata'], bins=50, color='blue')
    plt.xlabel('Airport Code')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.axvline(x=data['iata'].value_counts().idxmax(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Most Common Airport Code: {:.2f}'.format(data['iata'].value_counts().max()))
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of airport codes?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
